I was shown this film in my women's studies class, last month 09-2000. I really enjoyed it. I think it very important to all of us to realize how very lucky we are in our current life situations. I for one am attending a great univeristy, living in chicago, and am employed. I dont feel the need to have a man around am very, very content with life. This film made me feel extreamly grateful for my life. Not to say that the girls in the film had a terrible exsistance. This film just really touched me.
